    dc:creator "Venegas, Pablo J.; García-Ayachi, Luis A.; Chávez-Arribasplata, Juan C.; García-Bravo, Antonio" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "Four new species of polychromatic spiny-tailed iguanian lizards, genus Stenocercus (Iguania: Tropiduridae), from Peru" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6346004>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345984>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345986>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345988> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6346004>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Spiny-tailed species of Stenocercus in situ. (A) adult male of S. torquatus basking on a branch near Oxapampa town; (B) adult male of S. asenlignus sp. nov. basking in a tree near Omia (type locality); (C, D) adult female of S. torquatus hidden and perched on a roof support of a rural house; (E) an adult male of S. flagracanthus hidden at the base of a wall near Shipasbamba; and (F) an adult male of S. flagracanthus basking in a tree at Suyubamba. Photographs by (A) O. Custodio, (B) T. Mark, (C, D) A. Marchelie, (E) AGB, and (F) E. Calle-Alverca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6346004/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345984>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Stenocercus asenlignus sp. nov. preserved holotype, adult male, SVL 69 mm (CORBIDI 20219): dorsal (A), lateral (B), and ventral (C) views of the head; dorsal (D) and ventral (E) views of the entire specimen. Photographs by LAGA. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345984/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345986>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dorsolateral and ventral views of Stenocercus asenlignus sp. nov. in life: (A, B) holotype (CORBIDI 20219); (C) adult male, SVL 73 mm (MUSM 23034); (D, E) adult female, SVL 72 mm (CORBIDI 20220); (F, G) adult female, SVL 59 mm (CORBIDI 20135); (H) adult female, SVL 71 mm (CORBIDI 20217); (I, J) juvenile, SVL 32 mm (CORBIDI 20199); (K) adult male photographed basking in Omia (not collected); (L) adult male photographed in Omia (not collected). Photographs by (A-J) PJV, (K) LAGA, and (L) AGB." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345986/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6345988>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Stenocercus asenlignus sp. nov., Stenocercus leybachi sp. nov., S. nigrocaudatus sp. nov., and S. qalaywasi sp. nov., and the similar species: S. arndti, S. carrioni, S. chlorostictus, S. crassicaudatus, S. empetrus, S. eunetopsis, S. flagracanthus, S. simonsii, and S. torquatus. The symbols of species with a black spot in the centre correspond to type localities. Black dots correspond to important cities for reference." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6345988/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

